Given an integer array, find the contiguous subarray (at least one element) which has the maximum sum, and return that sum.

Example
nums = [-2,1,-3,4,-1,2,1,-5,4]
👉 Output:
6

Approach Kdane Algo: calculate sum of each index if sum becomes negative set currentSum = 0

fun main() {
 
    val nums = intArrayOf(1,2,-6,3,4,-5)
    var sum = 0
    var max = Int.MIN_VALUE
    for(i in nums.indices){
        sum += nums[i] // calculate sum
        
        if(sum > max){
            max = sum // store max
        }
        
        if(sum < 0){
            sum = 0 // reset to 0 when sum is negative
        }
      
    }
    println(" -- $max")
   
}
